<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-3074] comments and documentation for index_interval are misleading</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3074</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The comments and documentation for index_interval are misleading.  They state the larger the &lt;b&gt;sampling&lt;/b&gt; the more effective the index as at the cost of space.  This is true, but in the context of the configuration variable it implies the larger the &lt;b&gt;setting&lt;/b&gt; is the larger the index is while in fact it&apos;s the opposite of that.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
